    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-05T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="423"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d423">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">665.006/63: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-05T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 5, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. Your 84, February 21, 7 p.m. We are giving serious study to the Italian trade
                    problem, but before any decision can be reached it will be necessary to
                    formulate more definitely our policy with regard to the generalization of
                    concessions given to other countries as a result of trade agreement
                    negotiations. We will inform you as soon as possible of such decision as we
                    reach.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
